io.jsonwebtoken

Class JwtHandlerAdapter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.jsonwebtoken.JwtHandlerAdapter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object to return to the parser caller after handling the parsed JWT.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    JwtHandler<T>

    public class JwtHandlerAdapter<T>
extends Object
implements JwtHandler<T>
    An Adapter implementation of the JwtHandler interface that allows for anonymous subclasses to process only the JWT results that are known/expected for a particular use case.

    All of the methods in this implementation throw exceptions: overridden methods represent scenarios expected by calling code in known situations. It would be unexpected to receive a JWS or JWT that did not match parsing expectations, so all non-overridden methods throw exceptions to indicate that the JWT input was unexpected.

    Since:
    0.2

      • onPlaintextJws

        public T onPlaintextJws(Jws<String> jws)
        Description copied from interface: JwtHandler
        This method is invoked when a JwtParser determines that the parsed JWT is a plaintext JWS. A plaintext JWS is a JWT with a String (non-JSON) body (payload) that has been cryptographically signed.

        This method will only be invoked if the cryptographic signature can be successfully verified.

        Specified by:
        onPlaintextJws in interface JwtHandler<T>
        Parameters:
        jws - the parsed plaintext JWS
        Returns:
        any object to be used after inspecting the JWS, or null if no return value is necessary.
